Occupy Dallas: We Aren't Relocating
Group denies reports that it voted to pass its campground for a day
Friday, Nov 4, 2011 two | Updated 12:56 AM CDT


Occupy Dallas disputed news reviews Thursday that it would be shifting its camp from its current web page in the back of City Hall.
In a deal with the city, the group moved its campsite to City Hall Park almost three weeks ago. It has a permit to remain in the park until mid-December.
Occupy Dallas stated in a phone interview Thursday night that the group's General Assembly did now not keep a vote to move the camp to another location for a day.
"The notion exceeded around today was that we were going to surely easy out bad elements from our camp via regrouping for day at some other location. It was once scrubbed," the team posted Thursday night time on its Facebook page.
On Sunday, a convicted intercourse perpetrator used to be arrested on suspicion of having sex with a 14-year-old girl at the campground previously in October. The man and the teenager, who police stated was a runaway from Garland, were both staying at the camp.
Child Protective Services reportedly removed an infant from the camp. The group stated its members are attempting to discover housing for the family and employment for the father.
Occupy Dallas additionally stated that a "violent individual" used to be arrested at the campsite Wednesday night.
"We do no longer attract or generate unsafe people," the posting said. "People in office buildings, coffee shops and malls have to deal with loopy people, too."
The team also stated it did not have "a homeless problem," saying homelessness was now not causing any "logistical or criminal problems."
The crew advised NBC 5 it desires to have a higher grasp of who is in the camp. In a Facebook posting, Occupy Dallas stated it would announce plans shortly.